        "subject": "LU-4420 ptlrpc: Do not evict LWP connection.",
        "message": "LU-4420 ptlrpc: Do not evict LWP connection.\n\nRight now LWP connection will always be evicted during\nrecovery because quota needs to cancel all of the qsd locks\nby recovery, but FLD will also use LWP to lookup seq on MDT0,\neviction will cause unnecessary failure.\n\nSo we will not evict LWP, but fix the quota replay process,\ni.e. add a special flag LDLM_FL_NO_REPLAY, so these quota\nlocks will not be replayed but cancelled during recovery.\n\nAnd also remove fld rpc retry, because lwp import can handle\nreplay by itself with this patch.\n\nSigned-off-by: wang di <di.wang@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I31e8f3a1c860d7b0171b2cbd82421d16fef56862\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
